var cpFaqItems=[{id:1,category:"Working With Us",q:"How do we start working with Crest Point Media?",a:"The process starts with a conversation — not a proposal. We want to understand your business, your market, what you have tried before, and what success actually looks like for you. From there, we put together a scope that matches your objectives and budget. Reach out through the contact page and we will set up an initial call within 48 hours."},{id:2,category:"Working With Us",q:"What does a typical engagement look like?",a:"It depends on the brief. For integrated campaign management, most clients are on quarterly or bi-annual retainers that cover strategy, creative, media buying, and reporting. For project-based work — a product launch, an event activation, a rebrand — we scope per project. We do not have a one-size approach because the market does not work that way."},{id:3,category:"Working With Us",q:"Do you work with startups and SMEs or only large brands?",a:"Both. Our retainer tiers are designed to accommodate businesses at different stages. What we do not do is cut the quality of thinking based on the size of the budget. A smaller engagement means tighter scope, not lower standards."},{id:4,category:"Media & Creative",q:"What does your media buying cover?",a:"We plan and buy across television, radio, out-of-home (billboards, transit, airport, mall), digital, and print. Our buying is active in Lagos, Abuja, Port Harcourt, Kano, and Ibadan. For national campaigns, we coordinate across all major markets. We have direct relationships with stations, publishers, and OOH operators that give us access to placements and rates you will not get through a platform."},{id:5,category:"Media & Creative",q:"Do you handle creative production in-house?",a:"Yes. Creative production — concept development, copywriting, design, video production, and content creation — is done in-house. This matters because strategy and creative should not be two separate conversations. When the team thinking about where your message goes is the same team building what the message says, the work is more coherent."},{id:6,category:"Media & Creative",q:"Can you manage our social media channels?",a:"Yes. Social media management is part of our digital practice. We handle content strategy, content creation, community management, paid social, and monthly performance reporting. We do not offer templated packages — the strategy is built around your brand voice and audience, not a generic content calendar."},{id:7,category:"Pricing & Process",q:"How do you structure pricing?",a:"We work on both retainer and project models. Retainers are structured monthly, quarterly, or bi-annually. Project fees are scoped based on deliverables, timeline, and complexity. We are transparent about what drives cost and what can be adjusted if a budget is constrained. The conversation about pricing is part of the first call, not something we save for the proposal."},{id:8,category:"Pricing & Process",q:"How long does a campaign take from brief to launch?",a:"A fully integrated campaign with creative production and media buying needs a minimum of four to six weeks from a signed brief. Simpler activations — a digital-only campaign using existing creative — can move in two weeks. Timelines that are too compressed tend to show in the work. We will always be honest about what is achievable properly in a given timeframe."},{id:9,category:"Pricing & Process",q:"Do you offer reporting and campaign analytics?",a:"Yes, and we consider it non-negotiable. Every engagement includes a reporting structure agreed at the start — what we are measuring, how often we report, and what the benchmarks are. We use a combination of platform analytics, third-party measurement tools, and market research depending on the campaign scope. The goal is always to close the loop between spend and outcome."},{id:10,category:"Market & Expertise",q:"Which industries do you specialise in?",a:"We have active experience across financial services, FMCG, real estate, hospitality, healthcare, and entertainment. We also have a dedicated political communications practice working with candidates and public office holders across northern Nigeria. What cuts across all of these is the thinking — consumer insight, message architecture, channel strategy — not industry-specific templates."},{id:11,category:"Market & Expertise",q:"Do you work outside Lagos?",a:"Yes. We are Lagos-based but operate nationally. We have active campaigns and media relationships in Abuja, Kano, Port Harcourt, and Ibadan. For clients with a national footprint, we coordinate across all markets with consistent strategy and market-specific execution where the brief calls for it."},{id:12,category:"Market & Expertise",q:"What makes Crest Point different from other agencies in Nigeria?",a:"Honest answer: we do not over-promise. The Nigerian agency landscape has a lot of beautiful presentations and under-delivered results. We are built around people who have spent years executing, not just pitching — and our process reflects that. We will tell you what we cannot do as readily as what we can. Clients stay because the work is grounded in how the market actually works, not how it looks in a deck."}];

